Description:
Quality Renovation, Lifestyle Location, Private Courtyard
Superbly renovated and in a brilliant location, this unique and quiet apartment offers security entrance, bright living room with direct access out to a North facing private courtyard garden featuring Merbau decking as well as a Bluestone paved entertaining area, PLUS an oversized second private courtyard with direct access from the kitchen - ideal for those that love entertaining.
This just completed apartment has a fully equipped kitchen including stone bench tops, S/Steel appliances, dishwasher large bedrooms with BIRs, spacious designer bathroom with private laundry facilities And the added benefit of undercover security car park on title.
Conveniently positioned to the All New Ormond train station, North Road buses, local schools, EE Gunn Reserve with an off leash dog park and North Roads shops, cafes, supermarkets which makes for an enviable life style.

Description:
Family Bungalow, an entertainer's dream
Live, relax and entertain in superb space and timeless style in this impeccably renovated family Bungalow perfectly positioned to access excellent schools, parks, shops and CBD trains. Elegant period character and easy modern function are provided by its generous single level accommodation where formal and family living areas, alfresco entertaining spaces and up to five light filled bedrooms enjoy a leafy landscaped garden and excellent OSP. High Art Deco ceilings adorn a formal sitting room with OFP, adjoining dining room and the inviting main bedroom with BIRs served by an immaculate nearby bathroom. At the heart of the home, a premium modern kitchen follows an open design, linking formal entertaining to broad open plan family spaces, an undercover deck and private rear garden for successful entertaining. Other features include three additional bedrooms, all with BIRs, spacious home office/fifth bedroom with extensive storage, large laundry with shower and WC, granite kitchen, ducted heating/cooling, security alarm, pine floors, excellent OSP. Walk to Packer Park and locally renowned Left Field Cafe, minutes to Kilvington Grammar, buses, Carnegie and Ormond shops and stations.

Description:
Easy-care living with heavenly balcony
This sun-filled apartment provides an excellent opportunity for first home buyers, professional couples or astute investors given its central location, low maintenance ease & stylish interiors. Part of a boutique complex, it showcases a spacious tiled open-plan domain with feature kitchen including quality appliances, abundant storage & a convivial stone breakfast bench. Contemporary tones & finishes create a sense of designer style & functionality that are extended to the large bedroom with expansive mirrored robes & the pristine bathroom with stone vanity. A divine enclosed balcony offers panoramic views of the area & provides the ideal platform for summertime entertaining & weekend relaxation. Positioned for convenience close to Ormond shopping precinct & train station, this easy-care home also offers a car park & storage cage on title, secure intercom entry, split system heating & cooling & a discreet Euro laundry for added livability.

Description:
Space and Style for an Easy Life
Up in the trees and right at the front, this light-splashed two bedroom apartment surely is the pick of the bunch! Dishing up generous spaces and needing absolutely no work, first home buyers and investors would be wise to jump in quick to take advantage of a fine location only moments to Ormonds hub.
Securely accessed with a buzzer intercom, the homes dark floors add a designer touch to the superbly proportioned living and dining zone. Offering ample space for dining with friends adjacent the contemporary stone kitchen, there is also a large lounge to relax into the evening. Peacefully zoned, the bedrooms are both impressive, the largest retreat is a true king room, both take in calming leafy outlooks and benefit from lots of storage. An updated bathroom with stone vanity and convenient laundry taps is a smart inclusion, whilst a split system, air conditioner and onsite parking behind auto gates wrap up the easy-care offering.
Head out on the easy stroll to cafes, buses and the station and live the life that this premium suburb is so famous for.

Description:
Luxurious 5 Bed Home in McKinnon School Zone
Luxurious and most elegant home in McKinnon School Zone with five bedrooms, five ensuites and an exceptional dual kitchen with a full complement of Miele appliances. This oversized home features four principal living zones including a dedicated theatre room, dining with a gas log fire-warmed open plan domain and inbuilt mini-bar, extending to a polished concrete alfresco area overlooking the pool. A rumpus room and large balcony on the second level complete the perfect family entertainer.
5 Bedrooms, 5 ensuites, 4 living zones
Master bedroom with balcony, oversized WIR & Ensuite, Tuscany spa, double sink & shower
All bedrooms include a luxurious ensuite with shower (2nd master with bath & large balcony)
Executive kitchen with dual Miele ovens, 5 burner stove, indoor BBQ and boiling water tap
Butlers pantry with 3rd Miele oven and cooktop
Open plan pantry and feature display dividing cabinet
Theatre room system including subwoofer, projector, speakers, screen, receiver, DVD player
In-built solar heated swimming pool with a feature wall with a fountain with midnight lighting
Blinds, curtains, shutters and abundance of storage space throughout
Ducted vacuum with two hose packages upstairs/downstairs
Fully alarmed with surround security cameras & visual display
8 zone reverse cycle refrigerated air-conditioning include wifi control via smartphone
Double lock up remote garage with shelving
Fully landscaped with mature trees & plants, surround paving & polished concrete patio
A safe quiet walk to McKinnon Secondary College, McKinnon Primary School and Joyce Park, moments to Centre and North Road's exciting cafes and restaurants, Ormond station, the Monash University bus and McKinnon Reserve.

Description:
Position, Potential & Standalone Scope!
Why settle for just a unit when you can have standalone a dream home! A scaled-down version of a classic 1950's brick veneer Dream Home, this immaculate two bedroom home has the position and streetfront privacy of your dreams with a freestanding position, generous garden space front and rear, and a rewarding rail and retail strip location.
Rent or enjoy exactly as is and reap the rewards of a pristine kitchen with meals, generous robe-fitted bedrooms, Brivis ducted heating and air-conditioner there's even the security of roller-shutters and a secure garage plus driveway parking. Alternatively, see the scope to capitalise on this commuter lifestyle location with a clever renovation that makes best use of light-filled north-facing living, a vast and versatile separate-facility bathroom area, and a large laundry.
Invest, enjoy, add value and reap the rewardswhatever the plan, there's plenty to love in this high-amenity dream location within 250 metres of Ormond's restaurant and shopping strip, two blocks of the station and North Rd bus and a 27 minute commute to the CBD.

Description:
Quality, Charm, Accommodation & a Great Zone Location
Live with Art Deco appreciation, great accommodation and a coveted McKinnon College Zone location. A showpiece of its era extended from a solid-brick base, this original AVJennings home features lovely late period detail and family flexibility within a generous five-bedroom, two-bathroom floorplan.
Designed to optimise north sun with a grand formal lounge and a fifth bedroom large enough to double as additional living, this inviting home features well-designed bathrooms and a dedicated dining zone beside a modern kitchen.
Resplendent with sand polished floors, an impressive marble fireplace and curvaceous cabinetry, this centrally heated home has multiple reverse cycle air-conditioners, built-in robes and great approx. 6600sqft/613sqm grounds with room to entertain in lawned gardens plus plentiful parking including a tandem auto-garage.
Ormond addressed, McKinnon College Zoned and located on the bus-route to the tram, station, bay and Monash University, this is divine Deco living.

Options Aplenty on 565sqm Approx.
(EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSING 10th MAY 2019)
Make an exciting contribution to Ormond's ever transforming streetscape with this brilliant north facing block of some 565sqm (approx.). Positioned ideally on a tranquil, tree lined street you have the option to Renovate the existing home or explore the redevelopment possibilities (STCA) encouraged by a parcel of such superb size and scope. Be inspired by this quiet, family focussed area whose dynamic cafe culture, cosmopolitan shopping, acres of parkland and easy access to great schools and transport make it one of the South East's most rapidly evolving and highly sought after destinations. Walk to locally renowned Packer and Koornang Parks, Carnegie Swim Centre, popular Left Field Cafe, Ormond station and Koornang Road's vibrant dining and shopping precinct. Description:
Modern Perfection in Cosmopolitan Ormond!
For all your realestate needs contact Eric Cohen, at McKinnon Real Estate on 95780909
Step into this spacious, freshly renovated, single level modern home ideal for investment, retiree, or young couple starting off.
Positioned for privacy and quiet living, it boasts access to famous Left Field Café at the end of the street, and on to Paker Park Oval and playground.
Featuring 2 good size bedrooms both with built in cupboards and ceiling fans.
Hardwood Floorboards throughout, with a spacious lounge and dining room open plan design. Plantation shutters, and panel heater and A/c Split.
Modern Kitchen with electric induction cook top, electric oven, and dishwasher and more cupboard space.
Bathroom with bath and shower. Separate toilet, and separate laundry.
Outside courtyard with a side gate that can be used to store bike. Storage shed.
All the extras are here: Foxtel Broadband & Pay TV connection, 2 x security doors, security shutters to keep out the heat and cold. Instant H/water, 2 x A/c split systems, 2 x panel heaters, carport off street parking.
627 Bus will take you to cosmopolitan Chadstone or Elsternwick via all the zone 1 train stations including New Ormond station which is linked to southland shopping Centre.
Central to Ormond’s fabulous shops, restaurants, takeaways and cafes. IGA supermarket, dentist, doctors, children kindergarten and day centre are just some of the amenities for a busy family. Short distance to Caulfield pools, and Glen Huntly shops, cafes and Woolworths supermarket.
View by appointment or on designated open times

Description:
Solid period home with so many options!
Its hard to imagine an opportunity that delivers as many options as this one! A huge piece of land. The perfect orientation. A solid home, rich with history. Which of these will be the one to tempt you? Ideally located moments to Ormond shops & station and close to bus routes, this proposition is nestled in a location where Kilvington Grammar, parklands and recreation are also readily available.
With its origins firmly set in the 1920s, the home features geometric leadlight motifs, ornate ceilings and warm timber trim which star through the formal lounge with open fireplace and peaceful dining room next door - whilst a splash of groovy orange brings alive a super-cool dining booth adjacent the central kitchen. Up-to four bedrooms plus two bathrooms come as part of the package, along with a gas fireplace, split system, laundry and garage.
With such charming foundations, a sympathetic update and considered renovation could see this home become a fine setting for todays families. Alternatively, the ultra-accommodating allotment of land could swallow up a brand-new showpiece with ease still leaving space for a pool, alfresco zone and more - instead, others may choose to pursue a multi-dwelling development made possible by the stunning dimensions (STCA).

Streetfront Space & Modern Grace Within the Zone
Picturesque from the street, updated within and surrounded by shopping, transport and recreation amenity in the heart of the coveted McKinnon Secondary and Ormond Primary Zone, this streetfront home offers wide appeal for growing families, discerning downsizers and astute investors alike!
Intelligently designed with a vast lounge and garden-view dining at the front, a casual family zone to the rear and a private row of big robe-fitted bedrooms, this 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home displays leading edge interiors with stone benchtops and glass splashbacks in the Ilve appliance kitchen, streamlined cabinetry and engineered Oak flooring.
With room to lounge, dine and recline in a low maintenance paved courtyard, modern bathrooms including a stylish ensuite and a remote-controlled garage, the home enjoys exceptional extras including in-floor heating, split system air-conditioning, ceiling fans in every bedroom, secure alarm, and ducted vacuum.
Best of all, this superior single level has a premier location thats forever in demand nestled only metres from the highly regarded suburbs of Brighton East, McKinnon and South Caulfield. With Ormonds shopping strip and station nearby, the Hawthorn Road tram and Bentleighs vibrant shopping precinct within an easy walk, this McKinnon Secondary and Ormond Primary Zoned property has it all.

Description:
Prime Location at Exceptional Value!
A double-storey townhouse that has been cleverly designed to maximise the space provided, it features 3 great sized bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, a powder room and 2 living areas.
In a prime area close to the train station, schools and shops, Ormond offers a lively lifestyle where you'll enjoy having everything at your doorstep.
The kitchen boasts quality pendant lighting, a spacious bench top with room for a breakfast bar, a dishwasher, and plenty of cupboards and drawers.
All the bedrooms are conveniently tucked away upstairs and feature handy built-in robes, while the Master comes complete with a large walk-in robe and a fully equipped ensuite.
The garage has been converted into a storage room and a rec/study room with a split system aircon providing a great retreat for the kids. However, if you had other plans in mind for this space, it can easily be converted back.
Beautiful polished floorboards throughout and neutral colour tones are what sets this townhouse apart with the ability for you to easily decorate it and make it yours.
The low maintenance backyard features an undercover area allowing for easy entertaining with friends and family.
Additional highlights include an electronic door entry, evaporate cooling system, ducted heating for the whole house, and a security alarm.
Ideal for families, investors will also take comfort knowing this property is in an established area and one that is iconic to a blue chip location.
Call Lori Ille on 0490815632 today as this property won't be on the market for long.

Description:
Apartment Living with Homely Comforts
Lovingly maintained and occupied by the same owners for over 20 years, this private 2 bedroom first floor security apartment is immaculate. Situated at the back of the block, this light filled retreat enjoys an entry hall with storage, double glass doors to an inviting living room with balcony (clothesline), well-appointed kitchen/meals (electric cooktop, great storage), 2 large bedrooms (BIRs) and a radiant bathroom/laundry with separate toilet. With hard floors throughout including timber look floors in the living/bedroom spaces and tiles in the hallway, this idyllic first home or investment is equipped with security doors, gas heating, 2 air conditioners, security intercom and undercover parking. In a peaceful leafy street, an easy walk to North Road's shops, cafes, restaurants and transport including Ormond station and Chadstone & Monash University buses.

Description:
Create the Dream in the College Zone
An irresistible renovator, this rare 2 bedroom 2-storey Art Deco one of a pair is a fairytale opportunity to make it this delightful home something magical again. Retaining its classic ceilings, this homely retreat enjoys an entry foyer with loads of storage, a charming lounge, sun filled dining room with French doors onto a paved north facing courtyard garden; a retro 70s kitchen with electric stove, central bathroom, separate toilet, a large laundry and a lock up garage. The uniqueness of this home means the two lovely bedrooms (BIRs) are upstairs, yet feel connected with the home. With so much potential to add your cosmetic taste, change the layout and even extend, it's a fantastic vision to make it beautiful again. An excellent unit alternative with no common land, it's superbly located in the McKinnon Secondary College zone, around the corner from McKinnon Village, the train and Joyce Park, walk to North Road eateries and buses to Monash University.
